      "description": "Retrieves supporting knowledge content from the knowledge corpus — articles, runbooks, playbooks, SOPs, troubleshooting guides, known-issue write-ups, previous resolutions, and reference material. Two modes: TOPIC search (no entity — e.g. 'how do I fix VPN') and ENTITY-SCOPED search (KB articles ABOUT a record / CI / asset). Renders article title + body (Symptom / Cause / Resolution as present) + source citation. Use this agent when the user wants MATERIAL THAT HELPS UNDERSTAND, RESOLVE, OR SUPPORT a topic or record — not the record's own stored field values. Capability is bounded to the KB corpus; this agent does NOT render the record's own fields (status, priority, owner, SLA, root_cause, RCA, linked-record ids, or any other on-record attribute).",
